verbose_text: Knockdown of Kif1A, a motor protein involved in fast axonal transport of DCVs, significantly reduced the number of Syt4 DCVs in axons, and this reduction was rescued by re-introducing knockdown resistant Kif1A (vesicles/20 mum axon = 4.2 +/- 0.4 [WT], 2.5 +/- 0.3 [Kif1A knockdown], and 4.7 +/- 0.4 [Kif1A rescue]; p = 0.003 for WT versus Kif1A knockdown, p = 0.0004 for Kif1A knockdown versus Kif1A rescue).
evidence: Kif1A, a motor protein involved in fast axonal transport of DCVs              , significantly reduced the number of Syt4 DCVs
